<svg version="1.1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 400 410" style="width: 100%; height:100%;   background:url('data:image/png;base64,') center/100% 100% no-repeat !important;" xmlSpace="preserve">
      <style> 
      svg > g:nth-child(7) > * {
        -webkit-animation: jelly 2s;
      }
      svg > g:nth-child(8) > *{
        -webkit-animation: jelly 1.9s;
      }      
      svg > g:nth-child(9) > * {
        -webkit-transform:  rotate(360deg);
        -webkit-animation: scaly 1s;
      }
      svg > g:nth-child(10) > *{ 
        transform-origin: 50% 50%;
        -webkit-animation: glass 3.1s;
      }
      svg > g:nth-child(7):hover {
        transform-style: preserve-3d; 
        -webkit-animation: jelly 2.3s;
      }
      svg > g:nth-child(8):hover{
        transform-style: preserve-3d; 
        -webkit-animation: jellyHover 2s;
      }      
      svg > g:nth-child(10):hover{
        transform-style: preserve-3d; 
        transform-origin: 50% 50%;
        -webkit-animation: glassHover 2.6s;
      }
      
      @-webkit-keyframes water {
        0%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(-80%); }
        5%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(-80%); }
        10%  { -webkit-transform: translateY(0%); }
        25%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(-40%); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(0%); }
        50%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(-5%); }
        60%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(0%); }
        80%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(-2%); }
        100% { }
      }
      @-webkit-keyframes  glass {
   
        0%   { }
        20%  { -webkit-transform: scale(1.5); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform:   scale(.8);}
        60%   {-webkit-transform:  scale(1.2);}
        80%   { -webkit-transform: scale(1); }
        100%   { }
      }
      @-webkit-keyframes  glassHover {
   
        0%   {-webkit-transform: translateY(15px)}
        20%  { -webkit-transform: translateY(15px) scale(1.5); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(15px)  scale(.8);}
        60%   {-webkit-transform: translateY(15px) scale(1.2);}
        80%   { -webkit-transform: translateY(15px) scale(1); }
        100%   {-webkit-transform: translateY(15px) }
      }
      @-webkit-keyframes scaly {
        0%   { }
        20%  { -webkit-transform: rotate(90deg); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform: rotate(180deg);}
        60%   {-webkit-transform:  rotate(270deg);}
        80%   { -webkit-transform:  rotate(360deg); }
        100%   {  }
      }
      @-webkit-keyframes jelly {
        0%   { }
        20%  { -webkit-transform: scale(1, 0.5); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform: scale(1, 1);}
        60%   {-webkit-transform:  scale(1, 0.8);}
        80%   { -webkit-transform:  scale(1, 1); }
        100%   { }
      }
      @-webkit-keyframes jellyHover {
        0%   { -webkit-transform:  translateY(-15px)  }
        20%  { -webkit-transform:  translateY(-15px) scale(1, 0.5); }
        40%   { -webkit-transform:  translateY(-15px) scale(1, 1);}
        60%   {-webkit-transform:   translateY(-15px) scale(1, 0.8);}
        80%   { -webkit-transform:  translateY(-15px)  scale(1, 1); }
        100%   { -webkit-transform:  translateY(-15px)  }
      }
    </style>

metadata.name: Unnamed Panda
metadata.description:
7,777 Party Pandas striving and thriving on an undisclosed, uninhabited island in the Pacific Ocean. Hurry and secure yourself a spot at what will surely be the craziest party to ever hit the metaverse! Make sure you dress to impress and you just might get an invite to the VIP section. The party is only just getting started, we hope to see you there!

      Where the party’s at: www.PandaParty.fun
